<div class="ui people shape">
<div class="sides">
  <div class="side">
    <div class="ui card">
      <div class="image">
        <%= image_tag("better-notes.png") %>
      </div>
      <div class="content">
        <div class="header">Better Notes</div>
        <div class="meta">
          <span class="right floated">
            <a href="https://github.com/matt-stj/better-notes" ><i class="github icon large link"></i></a>
          </span>
          <span>
            <a href="http://recordit.co/Kp95sSSwIa" ><i class="world icon large link"></i>Demo</a>
          </span>
        </div>
        <div class="description">
          Better Notes is a desktop app built with Ember.js, Electron.js and FileBin.<br><br>
          It allows a user to create, read, update, or delete notes on their filesystem, as well as search notes by title/content and convert markdown notes to HTML.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="extra content">
        <span>
          <i class="circular inverted  grey tiny code icon"></i>
          Ember.js + Electron.js + FileBin
        </span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="side">
    <div class="ui card">
      <div class="image">
        <%= image_tag("rails-engine.png") %>
      </div>
      <div class="content">
        <div class="header">Rails Engine</div>
        <div class="meta">
          <span class="right floated">
            <a href="https://github.com/matt-stj/snow_alert" ><i class="github icon large link"></i></a>
          </span>
          <span>
            <a href="https://rails-engine-demo.herokuapp.com/" ><i class="world icon large link"></i>Live App</a>
          </span>
        </div>
        <div class="description">
          Use Rails and ActiveRecord to build a JSON API with endpoints that display business intelligence data from an online merchant database.<br><br>
          25+ RESTful API endpoints and Single-Responsibility controllers.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="extra content">
        <span>
          <i class="circular inverted  grey tiny code icon"></i>
          ActiveRecord + JSON API + AJAX
        </span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="side">
    <div class="ui card">
      <div class="ui card">
        <div class="image">
          <%= image_tag("twitter-curious.png") %>
        </div>
        <div class="content">
          <div class="header">Twitter Clone</div>
          <div class="meta">
            <span class="right floated">
              <a href="https://github.com/matt-stj/api-twitter-curious" ><i class="github icon large link"></i></a>
            </span>
            <span>
              <a href="http://twitter-curious.herokuapp.com/" ><i class="world icon large link"></i>Live App</a>
            </span>
          </div>
          <div class="description">
            Interact with your Twitter account through this look-alike app.
            With Twitter's OAuth and access to their API, you can view your feed, create new tweets, follow/unfollow users, and favorite tweets.
            This was my first exploration into OAuth and working with API data.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="extra content">
          <span>
            <i class="circular inverted  grey tiny code icon"></i>
            RoR + OAuth + VCR Testing
          </span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
</div>
